## Memorable Moments

**Vukradin sends Adabra six gold pieces via the postal system — five for the debt she claimed he owed, plus one gold piece of interest — using 'organic fair trade gold,' settling the score with maximum pettiness.**

*A pointed and petty response to Adabra's vicious personal attacks at the Druid Council, delivered with Vukradin's characteristic dignity*

> "Now that she's lost, she can have her money back."
> — Vukradin

> "It was brilliant! You turned everybody — you focused all of Adabra's rage on yourself and then walked out, rendered her arguments pointless and meaningless. She had prepared this whole vicious attack on you, and then, by leaving the field, you diffused it, enabling Soma to step in and to take over. It was brilliant. I haven't seen such brilliant oratory in my entire life. And then to do it on a matter of principle!"
> — Lyra

*Lyra gushing over Vukradin's dramatic walkout at the Druid Council, framing his principled exit as a masterwork of strategy*

**Brewbarry responds to Jenna Roscoe's condescending pitch about 'civilizing' an Uthgardian barbarian by letting out a loud, deliberate burp, sending her walking away.**

*Jenna Roscoe of the Lord's Alliance pushes too far with her recruitment pitch, earning the most eloquent rebuttal Brewbarry could muster*

> "Despite my looks, I'm not an idiot."
> — Brewbarry, just before the burp

**Vukradin delivers an impassioned speech about sustainable forestry and fair trade so moving that the illegal loggers put down their axes, burst into tears, and agree to report Tibor Wester's illegal camp to Neverwinter — aided by a natural 20 for a total of 27.**

*Faced with a dispute between novice druids and wildcat loggers, Vukradin turns a potential conflict into a moment of genuine moral transformation. Brewbarry wept, thinking of all the trees he had pulled from the ground with his bare hands.*

> "Voodoo, no touch. That's what Brewbarry remembers."
> — Brewbarry

*Brewbarry's entire wisdom on the subject of ghastly twig dolls bound with black hair, moments before Vukradin destroys one anyway*

**Vukradin destroys a twig doll and a still-beating pig's heart falls out; destroying the heart causes the dead tree's roots to erupt from the ground, trapping Boney and ensnaring Soma in the cursed clearing.**

*The party ignored Brewbarry's warning and triggered a dark magical trap hidden within the ritual site*

> "Horrible plan. Horrible. We do no touch. That's what Brewbarry said, you're not listening."
> — Brewbarry, watching Vukradin destroy more dolls after the roots erupt

**Valphine casts Daylight on her holy symbol in the middle of an attempted orc conversion, prompting the Talosian cleric to scream 'Kill the false cleric of Lathander!' and charge — turning a peaceful proselytizing attempt into an all-out battle.**

*The party tried to convert the orc warband to Lathander; Valphine's dramatic light show ended any chance of a peaceful resolution*

> "Kill the false cleric of Lathander! Kill… the drow cleric of Lathander, the abomination! Destroy! Destroy the false god!"
> — The Talosian Cleric

